Key Match Events: Diamondbacks' Corbin Carroll hit an inside-the-park home run in the first inning
Dodgers had back-to-back-to-back home runs from Shohei Ohtani, Mookie Betts, and Freddie Freeman in the first inning
The game was tied 6-6 by the eighth inning
Dodgers took an 8-6 lead in the ninth inning and held on for the win
Pre-Game Insights: The game drew over 50,000 fans, the second largest attendance at Chase Field
The Diamondbacks-Dodgers rivalry has heated up in the past year
Hispanic Heritage Weekend and Labor Day events were mentioned
Post-Match Reflections: Arizona manager Torey Lovullo noted the high energy of the crowd
Josh Bell compared the atmosphere to a postseason game
Miscellaneous Highlights: Diamondbacks play the Dodgers two more times on Sunday and Monday
